by julienfalque at 2020-05-23T18:48:45Z

The only annoying scenario I see is when a PR has an errors unrelated to its changes. For example: a method in `Tokens` that has wrong return type. Adding a new call to that method in some fixer will trigger a new error. The PR might either fix the return type and remove all related errors in baseline file but that will create a lot of noise. The other solution is to simply ignore the new error too, which is supposed to never happen. I'll try to fix most common errors in dedicated PRs to prevent this scenario as much as possible.
